The article is a statement by the President on the International Day Against Homophobia and Transphobia. The President emphasizes that lesbian, gay, bisexual, and transgender (LGBT) rights are human rights and that all people deserve to live free from fear, violence, and discrimination. The government is working to end bias-motivated violence, combat workplace discrimination, and address the needs of transgender individuals. The United States is also prioritizing the protection and promotion of LGBT rights in its diplomacy and global outreach. The President acknowledges that there is still much work to be done, but pledges to continue fighting for equality until everyone can live free and equal.